setTypeAndStates

public CharacterStateCell setTypeAndStates(CharacterStateCell.Type type,
                                           Set<CharacterState> states)
Set both the Type and states of this cell.

states will be copied so subsequent actions on it will not affect this cell.

Parameters:
type - the type
states - the states
Returns:
this cell
Throws:
IllegalStateException - if this cell is not a member of a row
IllegalStateException - if any member of states is such that state.getCharacter() == null, that is, if any of states isn't associated with a character
IllegalArgumentException - if any of states is such that state.getCharacter() is not the character of this cell's column
IllegalArgumentException - if type is Type.SINGLE and
IllegalArgumentException - if type is Type.POLYMORPHIC and states.size() < 2
IllegalArgumentException - if type is Type.UNCERTAIN and states.size() < 2
IllegalArgumentException - if type is Type.INAPPLICABLE and states.size() > 0
IllegalArgumentException - if type is Type.UNASSIGNED and states.size() > 0
